==English==
===Etymology===
:from [[vermin]] derived from Latin ''vermis'' meaning "[[worm]]". A term usually used in Westerns about undesirable animal pests or people.

===Noun===
#A pestering animal such as one that kills or harasses a farmer's livestock.
#A person who is obnoxious or makes trouble.

